nlist|\n* [[Ken Jeong]] \n* [[Jenny McCarthy]]\n* [[Nicole Scherzinger]]\n* [[Robin Thicke]]\n}}\n| host          = [[Nick Cannon]]\n| broadcaster   = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| winner-name   = [[Wayne Brady]] as \"Fox\"\n| image         = [[File:Wayne_Brady_2015.jpg|200px]]\n| runner-name   = [[Chris Daughtry]] as \"Rottweiler\"\n| last          = The Masked Singer (American season 1)\n| next          = The Masked Singer (American season 3)\n| year          = Late 2019\n}}\nThe second season of ''[[The Masked Singer (American TV series)|The Masked Singer]]'' premiered on September 25, 2019, following a \"special sneak peek\" on September 15, 2019.<ref name=\"Futon S2 Premiere\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/24/fox-announces-fall-premiere-dates-for-the-2019-2020-season-407510/20190624fox01/|title=FOX Announces Fall Premiere Dates for the 2019-2020 Season|publisher=[[FOX]]|via=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 24, 2019|access-date=June 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Fox Sets ''Masked Singer'' Season 2 Sneak-Peek Special|url=https://www.thewrap.com/masked-singer-season-2-sneak-peek-special-fox-t-paifall-t/|website=The Wrap|date=August 28, 2019}}</ref> Singer-songwriter [[Robin Thicke]], television personality [[Jenny McCarthy]], actor and comedian [[Ken Jeong]], and recording artist [[Nicole Scherzinger]] returned as panelists. [[Nick Cannon]] returned as host.\n\nSixteen celebrities compete anonymously in newly created full-bodied costumes including distinctive masks. Before each performance a video package teases clues to their identity with the celebrity narrating aspects of their biography in a disguised voice. After each performs in their own voice, the panel attempts to guess who is the masked singer. The contestants are later voted on to see who is safe and continues, or is up for a further round of singing in that episode, and possibly elimination.\n\n==Panelists and host==\n{{multiple image\n| total_width   = 420\n| align         = left\n| direction     = horizontal\n| header        = Season 2 panelists and host\n| image1        = Robin Thicke 2012 cropped.jpg\n| caption1      = [[Robin Thicke]]\n| image2        = Jenny McCarthy at E3 2006.jpg\n| caption2      = [[Jenny McCarthy]]\n| image3        = Ken Jeong March 2015.jpg\n| caption3      = [[Ken Jeong]]\n| image4        = Nicole Scherzinger 2012.jpg\n| caption4      = [[Nicole Scherzinger]]\n| image5        = Nick Cannon by David Shankbone.jpg\n| caption5      = [[Nick Cannon]] \n}}\nSinger-songwriter [[Robin Thicke]], television personality [[Jenny McCarthy]], actor and comedian [[Ken Jeong]], and recording artist [[Nicole Scherzinger]] returned as panelists. [[Nick Cannon]] once again returned as host.\n\n[[Anthony Anderson]] was a guest panelist on episode six, [[Triumph the Insult Comic Dog]] ([[Robert Smigel]]) was a guest panelist on episode seven, [[Joel McHale]] returned as a guest panelist on episodes eight and nine, and Season 1 winner [[T-Pain]] returned to the show as a guest panelist on episode ten.\n\n==Contestants==\nThe competitors were said to have achieved 140 films,  69 [[Emmy Award]] nominations, 42 [[Grammy Award]] nominations, 31 [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'']] #1 singles, 22 [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] shows, 20 [[RIAA|platinum]] records, 19 [[Emmys]] wins, 15 marriages, eight divorces, seven [[Super Bowl]] appearances, six [[multi-platinum]] records, five [[Hall of Fame]] honors, three [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''New York Times'' Best Sellers]], and two [[Time 100]] honors.<ref>{{cite web|title=(MS-201/2) \"Return of the Masks: Groups A & B\"|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20190910fox01/|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=September 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Youtube2\">{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=mxfvSnalXTo|title=Preview :The Number One Guessing Game is Back}}</ref>\n\nThe Season 2 winner, [[Wayne Brady]], had been asked to be on the first season of the show, but turned it down at the time. He said he felt viewers would tune in \"not because they want to see the talent, but because they want to see the train wreck.\" After he saw the success of the first season and getting approval from his daughter and ex-wife, he joined in for the second season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/features/the-masked-singer-winner-interview-wayne-brady-the-fox-season-2-1203447936/|title=''The Masked Singer'' Winner Interview: \u2018It\u2019s the First Time in My Life I Kept a Secret Months on End\u2019|first=Elizabeth|last=Wagmeister|date=December 18, 2019|accessdate=December 19, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; \"\n|- \n! rowspan=3 | Stage name<ref>{{cite web|last=Bentley|first=Jean|title=''The Masked Singer'' Season 2 Costumes Debut at Beverly Hills Fashion Show|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/see-all-masked-singer-season-2-costumes-1238886|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=September 12, 2019|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n! rowspan=3 | Celebrity\n! rowspan=3 | Occupation\n! colspan=\"13\" | Episodes\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |1\n! colspan=\"1\" |2\n! colspan=\"1\" |3\n! rowspan=\"2\" |4\n! rowspan=\"2\" |5\n! rowspan=\"2\" |6\n! rowspan=\"2\" |7\n! rowspan=\"2\" |8\n! rowspan=\"2\" |9\n! rowspan=\"2\" |10\n! rowspan=\"2\" |11\n! rowspan=\"2\" |13<!-- Leave as #13, not #12: Episode 12 is a recap/behind-the-scenes episode -->\n|-\n! A\n! B\n! C\n! D\n|-\n! Fox\n| [[Wayne Brady]]\n| Actor/comedian\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=#F888FD | WIN\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"lightgreen\" | SAFE\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"lightgreen\" | SAFE\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=#F888FD | WIN\n| bgcolor=\"lightgreen\" | SAFE\n| bgcolor=\"lightgreen\" | SAFE\n| bgcolor=gold | '''WINNER'''\n|-\n! Rottweiler\n|